        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/ecae2f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-02-15T18:28:44.408Z",
        "cooked": "<p>It would be useful to have the convenience of AI assistance to interact verbally when sending Signal messages and not need to solely send voice recordings when trying to use the service ‚Äúhands free.‚Äù Has there been discussion of any kind concerning AI integration that can be done using zero knowledge cryptography?</p>\n<p>Is there anything like this already under development that Signal might cooperate with?</p>\n<p>Along the same lines, does anyone here know anything about PIN AI which recently launched? They claim that their system will keep all user data private, with zero knowledge on the developer‚Äôs end. ‚Äì (PIN AI is not to be confused with AI PIN by Humane) If their claims are actually reliable, it could be very useful.</p>",
