        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/ac91a4/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-02-16T11:45:18.566Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Proton implemented an AI assistant for writing emails. They wrote <a href=\"https://proton.me/blog/how-to-build-privacy-first-ai\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">a blog post on how to do ‚Äúprivacy-protecting AI‚Äù</a> which is interesting to read.<br>\nBut that‚Äôs for <strong>email</strong>. Nowadays, businesses and some people expect AI to write and proofread emails for them. That is quite distinct from Instant Messaging, and I really don‚Äôt see the advantage of using AI in Signal at all.<br>\nNot just that many Signal users would leave Signal because of it, I don‚Äôt see what you would use it for, and it is a massive waste of resources. I highly doubt Signal Devs will implement something like that any time soon (if ever).<br>\nAnd that‚Äôs for the better anyway, IMHO.</p>",
