        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/{size}/34172_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-02-16T12:48:02.040Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Signal would need to do a lot of innovative, bespoke research and implementation to make something like this work, the same as they‚Äôve done with how they‚Äôve designed Signal.</p>\n<p>Since they‚Äôre a charity, the vast majority of the existing bespoke design took ~10 years to get to the current state. It would take even longer, and require exponentially more capital, for them to do the same for AI.</p>\n<p>Putting the technical aspects aside, the cost to hire AI engineers alone would be in the millions of dollars per engineer. Then you add the regulatory scrutiny and the costs start to become astronomical before any work has actually been done.</p>",
