        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/ecae2f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-02T02:59:09.044Z",
        "cooked": "<p>That Proton blog post was a good read. The concept the writer discussed in terms of an AI which is centered around user privacy is the type of thing that I‚Äôm watching for.</p>\n<p>PIN AI claims that their service will be completely private and will be capable of connecting to all kinds of sensitive private information securely and with ‚Äúzero knowledge‚Äù on their end like how Signal operates. The idea is that users can ask questions like ‚Äúcan I afford to buy this new car‚Äù or ‚Äúsend my mother a birthday present‚Äù and based on whatever you give it access to, the AI will take care of everything for you.</p>\n<p>I was half hoping that someone in the forum would be ‚Äúin the know‚Äù on PIN AI and be able to speak to whether their claims of a 100% private AI were feasible/ credible.</p>",
