      {
        "id": 262728,
        "name": "Ian Thurgood",
        "username": "Slartibartfast",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/ecae2f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-03T17:42:33.166Z",
        "cooked": "<p>You have a lot of good points there.</p>\n<p>The query started when I was thinking about the difference in accessibility feature between Signal and messaging services I had used previously for SMS/ RCS. Some of them were capable of interacting with a virtual assistant, for example, when I was driving. I kind of miss being able to hear messages being read out and then dictating a response, all hands-free. It came in handy when a lot was going on and I happened to be driving. (I prefer to take care of things in the moment rather than run the risk of forgetting to do it later)</p>\n<p>That was the impetus, but also I was curious if anyone thought that a 100% private AI was even possible. ‚Äì Or even an AI that was completely private on the individual level and securely using more than sufficiently anonymized data for anything that had to be handled at large.</p>",
