        "created_at": "2025-10-02T06:39:28.325Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Slartibartfast\" data-post=\"9\" data-topic=\"66935\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/ecae2f/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Slartibartfast:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I kind of miss being able to hear messages being read out and then dictating a response, all hands-free.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I believe there are some accessibility applications that can read out messages for you, maybe someone can point you to a specific one? A screen reader is possible without AI implementation (for some you might even be able to add personalized words for insider jokes). The same goes for dictating text to a certain degree (depending on the language and your personal vocabulary).</p>",
        "post_number": 10,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 12,
